  3.9123286462123804`*^9, 
  3.9123286654317408`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e83db88d-67c9-42b7-a64a-\
5253595cff1e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Diagonally-and-antidiagonally-dressed disjoint Bogoliubov diagrams with \
non-identical one-body vertices\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9123225301750393`*^9, 3.9123225545237913`*^9}, {
  3.9123286967354116`*^9, 3.9123287107977743`*^9}, {3.9123287715426073`*^9, 
  3.9123287814673014`*^9}, {3.9123311754152274`*^9, 3.912331189206489*^9}, {
  3.9123312232189016`*^9, 
  3.9123312276621213`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3f9140ac-a973-4b69-b6df-\
c05e7072eb1c"],

Cell["\<\
Depending on the components of the one-body potential into play, symmetry \
rules may apply and reduce the total number of fully-contracted terms. When \
the multiplied Nambu components of the one-body potential are distinct, no \
vertex exchange is possible. Additionally, since single-particle index \
transpositions within each one-body vertex are forbidden, no filtration \
process is necessary. Thus, the number of inequivalent \
diagonally-and-antidiagonally-dressed disjoint Bogoliubov contributions with \
non-identical vertices at second order remains equal to 8.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.912322579269453*^9, 3.9123226345921354`*^9}, {
  3.9123226697432995`*^9, 3.9123228694040194`*^9}, {3.912323377321495*^9, 
  3.9123233835289555`*^9}, {3.9123331180668077`*^9, 3.912333133784379*^9}, {
  3.9123337248637705`*^9, 3.912333725851756*^9}, {3.912334200112067*^9, 
  3.912334205774393*^9}, {3.912334269934724*^9, 3.9123342744885716`*^9}, {
  3.912334370889967*^9, 3.9123343803464336`*^9}, {3.912334773333669*^9, 
  3.912334773850529*^9}, {3.912334873982134*^9, 
  3.9123348793842125`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fae1e1fd-27d1-40be-aaab-\
1456a22a289a"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"For", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"u", "=", "1"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"u", "\[LessEqual]", "8"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"u", "++"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"Print", "[", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<CombBog[[\>\"", ",", "u", ",", "\"\<]]=\>\"", ",", 
